display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g \colon  B\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } C]]></fr:tex> to check that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f \colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00K7.xml"
title="Partial function"
addr="jms-00K7"
type="local">functional</fr:link>. Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c_1,c_2\in  C]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (g\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}}}c_1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (g\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}}}c_2]]></fr:tex>, we must check that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c_1=c_2]]></fr:tex>. By definition of the relational composite, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b_1,b_2\in  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f}b_1\mathrel {g}c_1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f}b_2\mathrel {g}c_2]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> is functional, we note that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b_1 = b_2]]></fr:tex>. Writing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b=b_1=b_2]]></fr:tex>, we therefore have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\mathrel {g}c_1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\mathrel {g}c_2]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex
